sql:
SELECT year
FROM climate_data
WHERE rcp26 = (SELECT MAX(rcp26) FROM climate_data);

SELECT MAX(rcp45) AS max_temperature_change
FROM climate_data
WHERE rcp45 IS NOT NULL;

SELECT DISTINCT source_name, source_id 
FROM data_sources 
ORDER BY source_name;

SELECT MIN(year) AS earliest_year_with_rcp45_projection
FROM climate_data
WHERE rcp45 > 0;

SELECT MAX(rcp85) AS max_rcp85_projection
FROM climate_data
WHERE year = 0 AND data_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- RCP (Representative Concentration Pathway) scenarios are a set of greenhouse gas concentration and emissions scenarios used by the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) for climate modeling and research; 
- Climate models are computer simulations used to study climate dynamics and make predictions about future climate change;
- The different RCP scenarios (rcp26, rcp45, rcp60, rcp85) represent different levels of greenhouse gas emissions and concentrations, leading to varying degrees of global warming and associated climate changes.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT researcher_id 
FROM data_access_logs 
WHERE access_type = 'view' AND query_params LIKE '%rcp26%';

SELECT AVG(rcp45) AS average_temperature_change
FROM climate_data
WHERE year IN (1982, 1992);

SELECT MAX(rcp85) AS max_rcp85
FROM climate_data
WHERE rcp85 IS NOT NULL;
